/* Colombians */ new section

PLOS is simply reaffirming other studies that state the average Colombian DNA is around 62% European 27% native and 9% African. Reference: https://web.archive.org/web/20151208130730/http://www.bdigital.unal.edu.co/29211/1/27220-95525-1-PB.pdf

There is absolutely no official count by the government that states Afro Colombians are (20%) of the population or that Indigenous Colombians are (10%). PLOS is simply reaffirming other studies that state the average Colombian DNA is around 62% European 27% native and 9% African. Reference: https://web.archive.org/web/20151208130730/http://www.bdigital.unal.edu.co/29211/1/27220-95525-1-PB.pdf

There is absolutely no proof of what you are saying. The same agency already conducted a separate study with Colombia’s white population and the numbers were vastly different then the ones conducted by PLOS for Colombians as a whole. Reference this here :https://rdcu.be/dvl10. Here white Colombians were shown to have 70-80% European dna. 80% of the population lives in the Andean region, meaning that a study measuring any major city from that region is more likely to grasp the average Colombian

/* Genetics */Replaced data from 2008 to data from the latest genetic study done on the Colombian population . The PLOS study was also conducted over a larger sample pool and actually specializes in genetic studies, making it a more reputable source then the previous one listed
